 GitHub Actions CI/CD + Digital Ocean Droplet Setup

 Context

 Set up CI/CD with GitHub Actions and deployment to a single DO droplet running two Django projects (identical stack, different domains). This plan covers
 the zenofewords repo — the second repo will replicate the same pattern.

 Architecture

 - Droplet: smallest DO droplet, single PostgreSQL instance, two databases
 - Reverse proxy: Caddy (automatic HTTPS, trivial multi-domain config)
 - App server: gunicorn (2 workers per project, systemd-managed)
 - CI: GitHub Actions — test on PR/push, deploy to droplet on push to master

 ---
 Part 1: GitHub Actions Workflow

 1. Create .github/workflows/ci.yml

 Single workflow with two jobs: test and deploy.

 Test job (runs on every push and PR):
 name: CI

 on:
   push:
     branches: [master]
   pull_request:
     branches: [master]

 jobs:
   test:
     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
     steps:
       - uses: actions/checkout@v4

       - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v6

       - uses: denoland/setup-deno@v2
         with:
           deno-version: v2.x

       - run: uv sync
       - run: uv run pytest
         env:
           SECRET_KEY: ci-test-secret-key

       - run: deno task test

   deploy:
     needs: test
     if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/master' && github.event_name == 'push'
     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
     steps:
       - uses: appleboy/ssh-action@v1
         with:
           host: ${{ secrets.DROPLET_HOST }}
           username: ${{ secrets.DROPLET_USER }}
           key: ${{ secrets.SSH_PRIVATE_KEY }}
           script: |
             cd ~/zenofewords
             git pull origin master
             ~/.local/bin/uv sync --no-dev
             ~/.local/bin/uv run python manage.py migrate --noinput
             ~/.deno/bin/deno task build:prod
             ~/.local/bin/uv run python manage.py collectstatic --noinput
             sudo systemctl restart zenofewords

 2. GitHub Repo Secrets needed
 ┌─────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┐
 │     Secret      │              Value              │
 ├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
 │ SSH_PRIVATE_KEY │ SSH private key for deploy user │
 ├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
 │ DROPLET_HOST    │ Droplet IP or hostname          │
 ├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
 │ DROPLET_USER    │ deploy                          │
 └─────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────┘
 ---
 Part 2: Droplet Setup Reference

 3. Create deploy/droplet-setup.sh

 One-time bootstrap script (run manually on a fresh droplet). Documents the full server setup:

 #!/usr/bin/env bash
 # One-time droplet bootstrap — run as root on a fresh Ubuntu 24.04 droplet.
 # After running this, clone the repo as the deploy user and create .env.
 set -euo pipefail

 DEPLOY_USER="deploy"
 PROJECT_DIR="/home/$DEPLOY_USER/zenofewords"

 # --- System packages ---
 apt-get update && apt-get upgrade -y
 apt-get install -y git curl postgresql

 # --- Caddy ---
 apt-get install -y debian-keyring debian-archive-keyring apt-transport-https
 curl -1sLf 'https://dl.cloudsmith.io/public/caddy/stable/gpg.key' \
   | gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/caddy-stable-archive-keyring.gpg
 curl -1sLf 'https://dl.cloudsmith.io/public/caddy/stable/debian.deb.txt' \
   | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/caddy-stable.list
 apt-get update && apt-get install -y caddy

 # --- Deploy user ---
 adduser --disabled-password --gecos "" $DEPLOY_USER
 mkdir -p /home/$DEPLOY_USER/.ssh
 # >>> paste your public key into authorized_keys <<<
 # cp /root/.ssh/authorized_keys /home/$DEPLOY_USER/.ssh/authorized_keys
 chown -R $DEPLOY_USER:$DEPLOY_USER /home/$DEPLOY_USER/.ssh
 chmod 700 /home/$DEPLOY_USER/.ssh

 # Allow deploy user to restart its own services without password
 cat > /etc/sudoers.d/$DEPLOY_USER << 'SUDOERS'
 deploy ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/systemctl restart zenofewords
 deploy ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/systemctl restart caddy
 SUDOERS

 # --- PostgreSQL database ---
 sudo -u postgres createuser $DEPLOY_USER
 sudo -u postgres createdb -O $DEPLOY_USER zenofewords

 # --- uv (Python package manager) ---
 su - $DEPLOY_USER -c "curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh"

 # --- Deno ---
 su - $DEPLOY_USER -c "curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh"

 # --- Clone repo (as deploy user) ---
 su - $DEPLOY_USER -c "git clone git@github.com:zenofewords/zenofewords.git $PROJECT_DIR"

 echo ""
 echo "Done. Next steps:"
 echo "  1. Create $PROJECT_DIR/.env (see .env.example)"
 echo "  2. Copy Caddyfile to /etc/caddy/Caddyfile"
 echo "  3. Copy systemd unit to /etc/systemd/system/zenofewords.service"
 echo "  4. Run: systemctl daemon-reload && systemctl enable --now zenofewords caddy"
 echo "  5. Run initial migration: cd $PROJECT_DIR && uv run python manage.py migrate"

 4. Create deploy/zenofewords.service (systemd unit)

 [Unit]
 Description=zenofewords gunicorn
 After=network.target postgresql.service

 [Service]
 User=deploy
 Group=deploy
 WorkingDirectory=/home/deploy/zenofewords
 EnvironmentFile=/home/deploy/zenofewords/.env
 ExecStart=/home/deploy/zenofewords/.venv/bin/gunicorn zenofewords.wsgi:application --bind 127.0.0.1:8001 --workers 2
 Restart=on-failure
 RestartSec=5

 [Install]
 WantedBy=multi-user.target

 5. Create deploy/Caddyfile

 zenofewords.com {
     reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8001

     @static path /static/* /media/*
     handle @static {
         root * /home/deploy/zenofewords
         file_server
     }
 }

 Note: when the second project is added, append another block for its domain pointing at :8002.

 6. Create .env.example

 Document required env vars for the droplet:

 ALLOWED_HOSTS=zenofewords.com
 DB_HOST=localhost
 DB_NAME=zenofewords
 DB_PASSWORD=
 DB_PORT=5432
 DB_USER=deploy
 DEBUG=false
 SECRET_KEY=
 SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=true

 ---
 Part 3: Update makefile + README + .gitignore

 7. Update makefile

 Replace old pip-based deploy target with uv/deno commands:

 pyc:
        find . -name \*.pyc -delet
        find . -name __pycache__ -delet

 deploy:
        git pull origin maste
        uv sync --no-de
        uv run python manage.py migrate --noinpu
        deno task build:pro
        uv run python manage.py collectstatic --noinpu
        sudo systemctl restart zenofeword

 8. Update README.md

 Short and to the point — project description, stack, how to develop, how to deploy.

 9. Add gunicorn>=23.0 to project dependencies

 Required on the droplet — add to main deps in pyproject.toml, run uv sync.

 10. Update .gitignore

 Add .pytest_cache/ entry (generated by pytest runs).

